This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with inferring the occupancy and semantic labels of a volumetric 3D scene from a single depth image. It also involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction and classification, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

It could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the ability to infer the 3D context information of a scene from a single depth image could be useful for robotic applications such as navigation and manipulation. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as CNNs, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Additionally, the use of 2D and 3D representations for feature extraction and classification could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper deals with volumetric data and geometric features, which could place it in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
